# ESP32 Portable WiFi Analyzer

A portable Wi-Fi analyzer built with an **ESP32-S2 Mini** microcontroller and an **OLED SSD1306 display**.

The device scans nearby Wi-Fi networks and displays useful information such as network name, signal strength, Wi-Fi channel, and security type.

The project is designed as a small portable tool for learning about Wi-Fi communication, ESP32 development, and embedded electronics.

---

# Features

* Scan nearby Wi-Fi networks
* Display signal strength (RSSI)
* Show Wi-Fi channel
* Detect Wi-Fi security type
* Display information on OLED screen
* Browse detected networks using a button
* Automatically rescan networks every 15 seconds

---

# Hardware

## Main Version

This project was created using:

| Component           | Function                           |
| ------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| ESP32-S2 Mini       | Main controller and Wi-Fi scanner  |
| OLED SSD1306 128×64 | Displays network information       |
| Push button         | Switches between detected networks |

## Compatible Boards

The project can also work with other ESP32-based boards, for example:

* ESP32 DevKit
* ESP32-WROOM boards
* ESP32-S3 boards
* ESP32-C3 boards

The pin configuration may need to be changed depending on the board model.

