# How It Works

1. The ESP32-S2 Mini starts in Wi-Fi station mode.
2. It disconnects from any existing Wi-Fi connection.
3. The device scans nearby wireless networks.
4. Information about detected networks is stored.
5. The first network is displayed on the OLED screen.
6. The user can switch between networks using the button.
7. Every 15 seconds, the device automatically performs a new scan.

