Signal: -55 dBm
Channel: 6
Security: WPA2
```

---

# RSSI Signal Strength

Wi-Fi signal strength is measured in dBm.

Because the values are negative, a value closer to zero means a stronger signal.

Examples:

| RSSI    | Signal Quality |
| ------- | -------------- |
| -30 dBm | Excellent      |
| -50 dBm | Very strong    |
| -70 dBm | Usable         |
| -85 dBm | Weak           |
| -90 dBm | Very weak      |

---

# Wi-Fi Channels

Wi-Fi channels are used to separate wireless networks and reduce interference.

If many nearby networks use the same channel, performance can decrease.

Common 2.4 GHz channels:

* Channel 1
* Channel 6
* Channel 11

The analyzer can help identify crowded channels.

---

# Security Detection

The analyzer can detect common Wi-Fi security types:

* Open network
* WEP
* WPA
* WPA2
* WPA3
* WPA2/WPA3

This helps identify whether nearby networks use encryption.

---

# Limitations

* The ESP32-S2 Mini supports only 2.4 GHz Wi-Fi.
* The analyzer cannot display passwords.
* The analyzer cannot see devices connected to a router without access to the router.
* The analyzer does not capture or monitor network traffic.
* Results depend on the Wi-Fi hardware and antenna quality.

